<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881104-0008 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief -- Vicon Fiber Optics Corp.: Fiber Optics Manufacturer, Affiliates Plan to Merge </HL><SO> </SO><CO> VFOX VTEL </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Vicon Fiber Optics Corp., Pelham Manor, N.Y., and two affiliates said that as part of a streamlining move, they will merge into a newly formed company called Syncon International Inc., subject to regulatory and shareholder approval.    Vicon and the affiliates -- Vitel Fiber Optics Corp. and Saxton Products Inc., based in Congers, N.Y., -- are engaged in different aspects of the manufacture of fiber optics, coaxial cable and related products.    Vicon owns 32% of Vitel and about two-thirds of Saxton. For each share of Vicon and Vitel common, holders will receive two-thirds share of Syncon and holders of Saxton will receive 7/12ths of a share in the new company, according to the proposal.    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Vicon closed at $2.0625 a share, up 6.25 cents. Vitel was quoted at $2 a share bid, down 12.5 cents, in national over-the-counter trading. </TEXT></DOC>